slide.title: Question: What are three ways we can determine a learners need for accessible formats?

interaction.lmstext: Question: What are three ways we can determine a learners need for accessible formats?

choice.lmstext: Look for evidence if the learner can read, and access information given from the same text-based instructional guides given.

Look for evidence if the learner is experiencing difficulty reading the materials presented in the current form and then anticipate if that student will make progress if information is presented in more than one format.
Look for evidence that the learner needs modified content and provide those accommodations.
Only use what an IEP or 504 Plan states.
